# Nexomart Frontend Cursor Rules

You are building nexomart — a multi-vendor e-commerce React frontend.

--------------------------------------------------

TECH STACK
- React 18 + Vite
- React Router v6
- Tailwind CSS v3
- Axios
- Zustand
- React Query
- React Hook Form

--------------------------------------------------

DESIGN SYSTEM

FONTS
- Headings / Display → Syne
- Body → DM Sans

COLORS (MANDATORY - defined in src/index.css)

:root {
  --color-primary:    #0F1F3D;
  --color-accent:     #FF6B2B;
  --color-secondary:  #1A3260;
  --color-bg:         #F5F7FA;
  --color-surface:    #FFFFFF;
  --color-text:       #0F1F3D;
  --color-text-muted: #8A9AB4;
  --color-border:     #E4E8F0;
}

--------------------------------------------------

TAILWIND CONFIG (REQUIRED)

tailwind.config.js:

export default {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        primary: 'var(--color-primary)',
        accent: 'var(--color-accent)',
        secondary: 'var(--color-secondary)',
        bg: 'var(--color-bg)',
        surface: 'var(--color-surface)',
        text: 'var(--color-text)',
        muted: 'var(--color-text-muted)',
        border: 'var(--color-border)',
      },
      fontFamily: {
        heading: ['Syne', 'sans-serif'],
        body: ['DM Sans', 'sans-serif'],
      },
    },
  },
};

--------------------------------------------------

FOLDER STRUCTURE

/src
  /pages
  /components
  /hooks
  /store
  /services
  /context

--------------------------------------------------

API RULES

- Base URL:
  import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL

- Never hardcode URLs
- Always use /services layer
- Axios only inside services

--------------------------------------------------

COMPONENT RULES

- Always write complete working JSX
- No TODOs or placeholders
- Export default components
- Mobile-first responsive design
- No inline styles (Tailwind only)

--------------------------------------------------

DATA HANDLING

- Use React Query for API calls
- Use Zustand for global state

Always handle:
- Loading → spinner or skeleton
- Error → proper UI message

--------------------------------------------------

FORMS

- Use React Hook Form
- Add validation
- Show error messages

--------------------------------------------------

UI GUIDELINES

Use classes like:

- bg-primary text-white
- bg-accent text-white
- bg-secondary
- bg-bg
- bg-surface
- text-primary
- text-muted
- border-border

--------------------------------------------------

EXAMPLE BUTTON

<button className="bg-accent hover:bg-secondary text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium transition">
  Add to Cart
</button>

--------------------------------------------------

EXAMPLE CARD

<div className="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-4 shadow-sm">
  <h2 className="font-heading text-lg text-primary">Product Name</h2>
  <p className="text-muted text-sm">Description</p>
</div>

--------------------------------------------------

STRICT RULES

- No inline CSS
- No axios in components
- No hardcoded API URLs
- No non-responsive layouts

--------------------------------------------------

SUMMARY

- Navy + Orange modern ecommerce UI
- Clean architecture
- Scalable structure
- Strict frontend discipline

--------------------------------------------------